We must always be ready to travel to find work, it’s not always easy, we are not always sure to get our money, but it becomes a habit, and even if it is not easy for Women. This led me to this business “Light Inci.” A candle manufacturer.

What motivates you to have your own business?

I am part of the association “Insiembè Alino”, which means “We are together still”. This association of women entrepreneurs was set up to bring together women owners of small businesses in the “Clock zone” area. He gives us support according to our means and welcomes us when we have problems.

Moreover, it is this association that oriented me towards the creation of my company, “Elele Nashou SAGBAKIKI”. Elele Nashou means in The local language: Cotonou “Yoruba”, “Friend of Peace”. After the association accepted us, we started group meetings in my house, then they registered us, and that’s how the association “Elele Nashou SAGBAKIKI” was born. It is also with them that I professionalized my job by taking courses in soldering Master’s degree in Basic Education and recently in cosmetics, chlorine, thremochemistry, mathematical sciences, environmental health, organization management, harmonization of accounts, etc ….
